Disease-Disease Associations and Visualization

Mustafa S Ascha

June 21, 2017

0.1 Motivation and Goals

  • Copious amounts of transactions data are produced not just in industry, but in healthcare claims
  • The curse of dimensionality makes explaining some of the relationships between item co-occurrence difficult
  • Solution: use visualization as a decision support tool–by displaying large amounts of data in concise ways, new patterns may be revealed

0.2 What we have

Data from Medicare synthetic PUF Sample 1. You can learn more about Medicare data here
